Comparing software outputs

Kornel Labun

21 mai 2024

1 Compare CHOPOFF methods

All methods from CHOPOFF return exactly the same results, despite different approach to the problem of off-target search.

nrow(linearDB_vs_treeDB)
## [1] 0
nrow(linearDB_vs_motifDB)
## [1] 0
nrow(linearDB_vs_prefixHashDB)
## [1] 0
nrow(prefixHashDB_vs_linearDB)
## [1] 0

2 Compare CHOPOFF to other methods

2.1 Compare CHOPOFF to CRISPRitz

We have loaded CRSIRPitz results and restricted it to maximum distance of 3, and removed duplicate alignments.

Guides that CRISPRitz finds and CHOPOFF does not:

nrow(crispritz_vs_prefixHashDB)
## [1] 0

As we can see, there are no such OTs. Now, OTs that CHOPOFF finds and CRISPRitz does not:

nrow(prefixHashDB_vs_crispritz)

2.3 Compare CHOPOFF to Cas-OFFinder
